Analysis: I found the leak! 
In `RouteState.java`:
```java
    RouteCursor cursorFor(RevisionLedger ledger) {
        RevisionFrame frame = ledger.current();
        if (cursor == null) {
            cursor = new RouteCursor(frame);
            return cursor;
        }

        if (!cursor.matches(frame)) {
            cursor = new RouteCursor(frame);
            return cursor;
        }

        return cursor;
    }
```
When `!cursor.matches(frame)`, a new `RouteCursor` is created and assigned to `cursor`, but the old `cursor` is never closed. `RouteCursor.close()` is what unpins the `RevisionFrame`. If it's not unpinned, the `RevisionFrame`'s pin count never reaches zero, so `closeLoadedGeneration()` is never called, and the `URLClassLoader` is never closed. This leads to a Metaspace leak.
Plan: 1. Modify `src/main/java/io/harbor/textd/core/RouteState.java` to close the old cursor before creating a new one.
2. Verify the fix by running the stress test again.

